(3. Continuous Scraping And Update Model) Tj
T*
(---------------------------------------) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(The parsing layer is intended to run constantly, not as a one-time import.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(3.1 Expected cadence) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(1. Start with hourly crawling for approved sources.) Tj
T*
(2. Promote stable, high-yield tier-1 sources to 10-minute cadence.) Tj
T*
(3. Keep partner/vendor/official sources on their own approved sync frequency.) Tj
T*
(4. Keep social and lead overlays slower unless they prove uniquely valuable.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(3.1.1 Fixture-first rule \(non-negotiable\)) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Before any source is run live, it must have:) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(1. offline fixtures under `tests/fixtures/<source>/`) Tj
T*
(2. parser regression tests that run with no network access) Tj
T*
(3. legal gate enforcement based on `legal_mode`, `risk_mode`, and `access_mode`) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(3.2 What must be stored for every discovered listing) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(For every found listing URL or listing identifier, the platform must preserve:) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(1. source name) Tj
T*
(2. external listing ID) Tj
T*
(3. listing URL) Tj
T*
(4. first seen timestamp) Tj
T*
(5. last seen timestamp) Tj
T*
(6. current status) Tj
T*
(7. raw capture reference) Tj
T*
(8. normalized canonical listing reference) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(This is the base requirement for ‚Äúall found property links.‚Äù) Tj
T*
